{{Other uses|Premise (disambiguation)}}

The '''premise''' of a [[film]] or [[screenplay]] is the initial state of affairs that drives the [[Plot (narrative)|plot]].

Most premises can be expressed very simply, and many films can be identified simply from a short sentence describing the premise. For example: [[E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial|''A lonely boy is befriended by an alien'']]; [[Jaws (film)|''A small town is terrorized by a shark'']]; [[The Sixth Sense|''A small boy sees dead people'']].

