{{Infobox organization | name = Switchboard | logo = Switchboard (UK) logo.png | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map2 = | map2_size = | map2_alt = | map2_caption = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | merged = | successor = | formation = {{start date and age|1974|03}} | founder = | founding_location = [[London]] | extinction = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | type = [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]] | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = 296193 | status = [[Charitable organization]] | purpose = | headquarters = | location = | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} --> | region = | services = [[Telephone counseling]] | products = | methods = | fields = | membership = | membership_year = | language = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = | leader_name = | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = | parent_organization = | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | staff = 1<ref>{{cite web|title=Volunteer|url=http://switchboard.lgbt/volunteer/|publisher=Switchboard|accessdate=18 May 2016|quote=We only have one paid member of staff}}</ref> | staff_year = | volunteers = | volunteers_year = | slogan = | mission = | website = {{URL|http://www.switchboard.lgbt|switchboard.lgbt}} | remarks = | formerly = London Lesbian and Gay Switchboard | footnotes = }}
[[File:London Lesbian and Gay Switchboard banner at Pride London 2010.jpg|thumb|London Lesbian and Gay Switchboard group at Pride London 2010.]] '''Switchboard'''<ref name="llgs to switchboard">{{cite news|last1=Duffy|first1=Nick|title=London Lesbian and Gay Switchboard changing its name to be ‘more inclusive’|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/06/24/london-lesbian-and-gay-switchboard-is-changing-its-name-to-be-more-inclusive/|accessdate=18 May 2016|work=PinkNews|date=24 June 2015}}</ref> is the oldest [[LGBT|LGBT+]] telephone [[helpline]] in the [[United Kingdom]], based in [[London]].
Switchboard was founded in March 1974 as the '''London Lesbian and Gay Switchboard''', providing help and information to London's [[gay community]], particularly in the aftermath of the partial decriminalisation of male homosexuality in 1967.
In the 1980s, Switchboard was the leading source of information on [[HIV/AIDS]], with some of Switchboard's volunteers amongst the founding members of the [[Terrence Higgins Trust]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tht.org.uk/our-charity/Our-work/Our-history/1980s|title=Terrence Higgins Trust in the 1980s {{!}} Terrence Higgins Trust|last=Trust|first=Terrence Higgins|website=www.tht.org.uk|language=en|access-date=2017-05-23}}</ref>.
In 2008, Switchboard was the recipient of the [[Queen's Award for Voluntary Service]]. The organisation was invited and accepted to go to [[Buckingham Palace]] to collect the award. In 2014, [[Queen Elizabeth II]] acknowledged the 40th anniversary of the organisation's founding, marking the first time she has had any involvement, voiced support or recognised an [[LGBT]] charity during her reign, and the first time the Crown has ever publicly supported the LGBT community.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hear, Hear! Queen Elizabeth Makes First Gesture of Goodwill to the LGBT Community|url=http://www.passportmagazine.com/blog/archives/35130-here-here-queen-elizabeth-makes-first-gesture-of-goodwill-to-the-lgbt-community/|website=Passport magazine|accessdate=12 July 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019104841/http://www.passportmagazine.com/blog/archives/35130-here-here-queen-elizabeth-makes-first-gesture-of-goodwill-to-the-lgbt-community/|archivedate=19 October 2015|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref><ref name="towleroad">{{cite news|url=http://www.towleroad.com/2014/03/queen-elizabeth-ii-congratulates-glbt-charity-organization-on-40th-anniversary.html |title=Queen Elizabeth II Congratulates GLBT Charity Organization On 40th Anniversary |publisher=Towleroad |accessdate=10 March 2014}}</ref> LLGS received a comment from the Queen saying: “Best wishes and congratulations to all concerned on this most special anniversary.”<ref name="passportmagazine">{{cite web |url=http://www.passportmagazine.com/blog/archives/35130-here-here-queen-elizabeth-makes-first-gesture-of-goodwill-to-the-lgbt-community/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-06-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019104841/http://www.passportmagazine.com/blog/archives/35130-here-here-queen-elizabeth-makes-first-gesture-of-goodwill-to-the-lgbt-community/ |archivedate=2015-10-19 |df= }}</ref><ref name="towleroad"/>
Switchboard rebranded to its current name in 2015 to emphasize inclusion for persons of all sexual orientation and gender identities, and that its services are not limited to London.<ref name="llgs to switchboard" />
Today, it has expanded considerably to more than 30,000 callers each year, and now also provides support through email and instant messaging. Switchboard provides a listening service for people to discuss their feelings in an impartial and non-judgmental way, as well as information and advice for going out in London and the UK. Switchboard also operates an internet database of LGBT+ organisations in the UK known as "queery".
